<div id="right">
    <div class="padding">
      <h1>Documentation</h1>
      <p class="path"> <a href="/en/docs/">Documentation</a>
</p>
 <!-- Content -->
<p>This part of the CERIT-SC portal aims to <strong>introduce</strong> you <strong> all the specifics of accessing the CERIT-SC computing resources and applications.</strong>.</p>
<p><em>Since most of our users have a previous experience with the MetaCentrum NGI (National Grid Infrastructure), the provided information <strong>supposes basic experience</strong> with job submissions via </em>PBS/Torque<em> scheduling systems. For more detailed (i.e., supposed) information, let us refer you to <a href="http://metavo.metacentrum.cz/en/docs/index.html">MetaCentrum site</a>.</em></p>
<div class="warning">
<div class="label">Important</div>
<div class="content">If <strong>anything stated here won't work for you</strong> or if you just need an <strong>advice</strong> regarding anything not mentioned here, please, write an email to <strong>CERIT-SC support staff</strong>: <a href="mailto:support@cerit-sc.cz">support@cerit-sc.cz</a> (Your email will create a ticket in the national e-infrastructure RT system (CERIT-SC queue), thanks to which you'll gain a detailed information about the process of resolution of your request/question).
<p>To accelerate the execution of the issues, which are supposed to be <strong>caused by the MetaCentrum infrastructure resources</strong> (e.g., problems with the <code>/storage</code> volume, problems with modules' availability/configuration), please, direct your requests to the <strong>MetaCentrum technical support</strong>: <a href="mailto:meta@cesnet.cz">meta@cesnet.cz</a> (improperly assigned requests will be internally exchanged between the technical support teams).</p>
</div>
